{"command":"create","path":"/workspace/regular_clean.sh","file_text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

# regular_clean.sh - perform regular cleanup tasks
# This script performs a few safe, common cleanup operations suitable
# for development workspaces. It avoids destructive operations unless
# running as root (e.g., apt-get autoremove).

# Find and remove Python bytecode files and __pycache__ directories
find . -type f -name '*.py[co]' -print -delete || true
find . -type d -name '__pycache__' -print -exec rm -rf {} + || true

# If running as root and apt-get is available, perform safe apt cleanup
if command -v apt-get >/dev/null 2>&1 && [ "$(id -u)" -eq 0 ]; then
  apt-get autoremove -y || true
  apt-get clean || true
fi

# Remove files older than 7 days from /tmp (if it exists) and ./tmp
if [ -d "/tmp" ]; then
  find /tmp -type f -mtime +7 -print -delete || true
fi
if [ -d "./tmp" ]; then
  find ./tmp -type f -mtime +7 -print -delete || true
fi

echo "Regular cleanup completed."
"}
